<DIV2 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>The Attestation of Mr. Covel an English Gentleman.</HEAD>
<P>MR. <HI>William Joseph Grelot,</HI> whom I familiarly
knew, while we both resided in <HI>Constantinople,</HI>
shew'd me at <HI>Paris</HI> certain Draughts, delineated with
his own hand, of the Cities of <HI>Constantinople, Ga|lata,
Scutari;</HI> as also of <HI>Sancta Sophia,</HI> and some
other Mosquees erected by the <HI>Turkish</HI> Emperours.
Therefore that I may not be wanting in the duty of a
friend, or asserting the truth, I am bound to confess,
that I know not well how sufficiently to extoll the Inge|nuity,
Industry and Diligence of the person; for I must
acknowledge, that all his Draughts, as far as I am able
