<P><HI>D.</HI> The Gate thorow which the Grand Signor enters in
to <HI>Sancta Sophia,</HI> when he goes to his Devotions.</P>
<P><HI>E.</HI> One of the Towers of <HI>Sancta Sophia,</HI> to the top of
which the <HI>Muezins,</HI> or Cryers, ascend, to give the
people notice of Prayer time: The Doors of the Gal|leries
to these <HI>Minarets,</HI> or Towers, are always turn'd
toward <HI>Koble,</HI> or the Coast of <HI>Mecca,</HI> to the end
